New Lead Form Submission\n\nServes an n8n-hosted form (Email, Company, Score). Each submission becomes one execution.\n\nNext: Stamp & Shape Lead","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"f52dc38f-49c9-f032-ae29-09fcc49dff8f","name":"Note: New Lead Form Submission"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp & Shape Lead\n\nShapes the item: writes `leadId`, `receivedAt`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Payload Valid?","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"6551a672-344d-60ac-280a-4bd7b4887b43","name":"Note: Stamp & Shape Lead"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Payload Valid?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.leadId }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Route by Work Type · ②→ Record Rejected Input","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"e45fe428-2d13-753d-4a72-3cf28abcb7ce","name":"Note: Payload Valid?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Rejected Input\n\nhubspot — `contact` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 HubSpot private-app token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,1030],"id":"a4293361-4ad0-0e1e-84a8-97cc5b367861","name":"Note: Record Rejected Input"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Route by Work Type\n\nRoutes each item to one of 3 lanes: mql, sql + fallback.\n\nPorts: ①→ Process 'mql' → HubSpot · ②→ Fast-Track 'sql' + Alert · ③→ Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"7a06f708-f011-5f2c-5aa2-0d4c787cf3be","name":"Note: Route by Work Type"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Process 'mql' → HubSpot\n\nhubspot — `contact` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Routed Work · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 HubSpot private-app token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,250],"id":"862db0a4-d209-0f09-b368-c168bd603f0d","name":"Note: Process 'mql' → HubSpot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fast-Track 'sql' + Alert\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Routed Work · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1290,760],"id":"bb28675f-c0de-18e0-aace-f58c42069520","name":"Note: Fast-Track 'sql' + Alert"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)\n\nhubspot — `contact` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Merge Routed Work · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 HubSpot private-app token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1614,1270],"id":"2b242c3a-f1bc-cc88-5d64-42926e8adc5a","name":"Note: Hold Unknown Types (DLQ)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Merge Routed Work\n\nRejoins 3 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Guard Non-Empty email","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2262,520],"id":"85a7939c-027b-c510-cbe2-a9ed40948bdf","name":"Note: Merge Routed Work"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Guard Non-Empty email\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Stamp Processing Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3234,520],"id":"b743c3f8-3ace-9063-47e8-c5734e0f94e6","name":"Note: Guard Non-Empty email"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Processing Time\n\nStamps `processedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Cap Batch Volume","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,520],"id":"08d0e7c3-0867-7d3e-65ec-1d98d3370400","name":"Note: Stamp Processing Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 25 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Save Execution Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3882,520],"id":"8d1afe35-660e-c551-f0c7-dcbc9c6a9cc3","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Align Field Names","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4206,520],"id":"a72bbd95-1124-ccbb-16d7-8a0181da8a0a","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Align Field Names\n\nNormalizes field names so every source feeds the same downstream schema.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"675609eb-0f4a-40fd-5907-55dc2710c9be","name":"Note: Align Field Names"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (HubSpot)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"9a9ab3ec-7cd5-66b1-0979-e4dd5385794b","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (HubSpot)\n\nhubspot — `contact` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Gmail · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 HubSpot private-app token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"60a1d5a7-69d9-a87c-a38a-e861db5f972d","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (HubSpot)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Gmail\n\ngmail — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"25011619-a30d-6d83-0afa-8932cd28ce71","name":"Note: Send Summary to Gmail"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,1540],"id":"017f1443-4ca1-9484-7f0d-f60d59cf5c26","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,1540],"id":"78c709f8-5127-9618-d6e6-e5b070af6ebc","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Capture inbound leads with HubSpot and Gmail without manual work\n\n**Pattern:** Lead Capture & Routing · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Form\n\n## What it does\nCapture inbound leads with HubSpot and Gmail without manual work. It starts from a hosted form submission.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual routing is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nNew Lead Form Submission → Stamp & Shape Lead → Payload Valid? → Route by Work Type → Process 'mql' → HubSpot → Merge Routed Work → Guard Non-Empty email → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to lead capture & routing without manual effort\n- Anyone automating routing in sales\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2; HubSpot private-app token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"a3cff9af-7d42-6405-c988-fd43ec114e08","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-290],"id":"d3516b39-ad5a-18c7-c95f-17fb3ac273ed","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your routing process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-290],"id":"31a4f946-ef82-138b-d4dd-8b028443c1c1","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"New Lead Form Submission":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp & Shape Lead","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp & Shape Lead":{"main":[[{"node":"Payload Valid?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Payload Valid?":{"main":[[{"node":"Route by Work Type","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Record Rejected Input","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Route by Work Type":{"main":[[{"node":"P